      • nullValues

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> nullValues()
        This method looks at what attributes are "uninitiated" in the class. i.e are null or have 0 value it will then return an array containing messages to be sent to the customer so that he can send back the values of the attributes. For example, if the name is null, then the arrayList will contain a message asking the customer to input his name.
        Returns:
        array of messages useful for the customer
